comments.body:
Added note:
{quote}
Important: Choose names and use them consistently for all NCs (both the file name ifcfg-br0 and the DEVICE=br0 in the file).
{quote}

[~lincoln.thomas] please review and approve. thank you!

If you have set up the network interfaces correctly in the "Configure Bridges" section of the install steps, there's nothing else you should have to do in upgrades.

[~kmeredith], this looks good to me. 

If people haven't set things up right, they would see the problem when they try to live-migrate. We could help them by saying something in http://packages.release.eucalyptus-systems.com/documentation/origin/master/admin-guide/manage_nodes.html#manage_nodes like:

{quote}
If the migration fails, check the {{nc.log}} file on the source and destination NCs. If you see an error similar to:
{noformat}
libvirt: Cannot get interface MTU on 'br0': No such device (code=38)
{noformat}
...then ensure the NCs have the same interface and bridge device names, as described in http://packages.release.eucalyptus-systems.com/documentation/origin/master/#install-guide/configuring_bridge.html .
{quote}

Whaddyathink?
